- **Processing Cells**: For each cell (i, j):
  - If reachable at an even second (`dp0[i][j]` is not infinity), transition to an odd second by adding the waiting cost (`waitCost[i][j]`) and update `dp1[i][j]` if this yields a lower cost.
  - If reachable at an odd second (`dp1[i][j]` is not infinity), move to adjacent cells (right or down) if within grid bounds. The entry cost for the new cell is computed and used to update the corresponding `dp0` entry for the new cell (next second is even).
- **Result**: The minimal cost to reach the destination (m-1, n-1) is the lesser value between `dp0[m-1][n-1]` and `dp1[m-1][n-1]`, representing the cost at the destination regardless of whether the last step was an even or odd second.

